The paper focuses on the generation of neural network architectures for computer vision tasks, specifically image classification. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses Q-Learning and epsilon-greedy exploration strategy, which are common techniques in machine learning and reinforcement learning, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the optimization of network blocks, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper proposes a distributed asynchronous framework, which could be relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
